{"title": "Absurdly Dedicated Worker", "content": "Yosemite Sam: My orders from General Lee is to hold the Masy-Dixy Line, and no Yankee's a-crossin' it! \n\nBugs Bunny: \"General Lee\"? Why, the War Between the States ended almost ninety years ago! \n\nYosemite Sam: I'm no clock-watcher! My orders from General Lee is to hold the Masy-Dixy Line, and no Yankee's a-crossin' it!\"General Lee\"? Why, the War Between the States ended almost ninety years ago!I'm no clock-watcher!\n\nA machine or creature is programmed to perform specific kinds of duties, but at some point in time, something happens to its environment that makes continuing to perform the task pointless. The machine, ever faithful, keeps doing it anyway since it was never told to stop. Often, this is a result of After the End or at least all humans leaving the place and forgetting the machine. Being unable to carry out its task may cause further problems.\n\nIt can also happen to a person if he is somehow traumatized and has become a stoic being with no sense of his surroundings, or when working in (relative) isolation where they can miss crucial information that renders their task pointless. See Real Life examples for these.\n\nSee also \"Sorcerer's Apprentice\" Plot, Bothering by the Book and The Determinator. Can overlap with Offscreen Inertia if the servant in question is revisited later in the story.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AbsurdlyDedicatedWorker", "links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/LooneyTunes", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AfterTheEnd", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnfulfilledPurposeMisery", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RealLife", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SorcerersApprenticePlot", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BotheringByTheBook", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheDeterminator", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OffscreenInertia", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/ECComics", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RoboticSpouse", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Flashpoint", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Runaways